---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaSection from '../components/CtaSection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How It Works | HeatherAI" description="The data, intelligence, and peer-reviewed science behind HeatherAI's coaching methodology.">

  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6 md:px-12 text-center">
    <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">The intelligence behind<br /><em class="not-italic text-accent">HeatherAI.</em></h1>
    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/50 max-w-[680px] mx-auto leading-relaxed">
      Most AI nutrition tools are built on textbooks. HeatherAI is built on twenty years of
      real coaching — 5,000 clients, a million messages, and the patterns that no one else has.
    </p>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ SECTION 1: THE DATASET ============ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">
          The dataset no one else can build.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white/50 max-w-[680px] mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          HeatherAI's coaching intelligence comes from four data sources spanning Heather Bauer's
          entire 20-year practice. Together, they form the largest longitudinal expert nutrition
          coaching dataset in existence — and it's irreproducible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Data source cards -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">
        <div class="p-8 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">01</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">1M+ Coaching Messages</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Two-way text conversations between Heather and thousands of clients, captured in real
            time over years. Not surveys. Not food diaries. Real coaching moments — food photos,
            restaurant menus, daily weigh-ins, post-vacation resets — all with the emotional and
            behavioral context attached. When a client texts "202, up 3 from last week, that work
            trip killed me," the number comes with the story.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">02</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">20,000+ Session Notes</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Detailed coaching session summaries capturing what texting misses: strategic planning,
            life context, medication changes, structured action items. Each summary is a window
            into Heather's clinical coaching rhythm — the part of coaching that happens between
            the daily texts.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">03</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">5,000+ Intake Profiles</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Starting weight, goal weight, medical history, dietary preferences, lifestyle context.
            The baseline that makes personalization real. When HeatherAI meets a new user, it's
            drawing on five thousand previous starting points to recognize which patterns are
            likely to emerge.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">04</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Ongoing Multi-Modal Capture</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            The dataset isn't static. Older clients provide historical depth — years of
            longitudinal text coaching. Current clients provide multi-modal richness — texts,
            session notes, and intake data overlapping in time. The intelligence gets deeper
            every week.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Irreproducibility callout -->
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-accent/20 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Why this can't be replicated.</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          To build this dataset from scratch, a competitor would need:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-white/55 leading-relaxed">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
            <span>A single expert with 20+ years of consistent coaching methodology</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
            <span>~5,000 clients coached over multi-year timescales</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Text-based coaching (not just in-person appointments) to capture real-time moments</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Clients willing to share food photos, weight data, and emotional context over messaging</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent mt-0.5 shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
            <span>All of it exported, linked, and queryable</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/70 font-medium leading-relaxed mt-6 text-center">
          That combination took Heather's entire career to create. It doesn't exist anywhere else.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ SECTION 2: THE INTELLIGENCE ============ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">
          What the data taught us.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white/50 max-w-[680px] mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          We didn't just collect the data. We analyzed it. What emerged were thousands of
          patterns — organized into five categories of coaching intelligence that HeatherAI
          uses in every conversation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-12">

        <!-- Archetypes -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-2">01 &middot; Archetypes</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Coaching Archetypes</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <em class="not-italic text-white/75 font-medium">Dozens identified. More emerging at scale.</em>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Not every client struggles the same way. Our analysis revealed distinct coaching archetypes —
            patterns of behavior, engagement, and struggle that repeat across thousands of clients. The
            disciplined daily logger who needs tactical food substitutions. The sporadic executive who
            needs restaurant menu pre-gaming before business dinners. The dropout-returner who needs zero
            judgment when they come back after months. The achiever-under-siege who needs empathy before action.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            When you start using HeatherAI, it identifies which archetype you match — and adjusts its
            entire coaching posture accordingly. Not generic advice. Coaching shaped by how people like
            you have actually succeeded.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Trigger Playbooks -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-2">02 &middot; Playbooks</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Trigger Playbooks</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <em class="not-italic text-white/75 font-medium">Hundreds of real situations. Each paired with a response that actually worked.</em>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            We cataloged the specific situations that cause clients to struggle — and paired each with
            Heather's proven coaching response. Workplace food environments. Post-vacation resets. Night
            shifts. Hormonal cycles. Business dinners. Sugar cravings at 10pm. Stress-eating after a
            hard day. IVF hormones. Holiday spirals.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Each trigger has a playbook — not guessed from a textbook, but extracted from real moments
            when Heather got it right. When HeatherAI detects a trigger in your conversation, it retrieves
            the matching playbook and coaches you through it the way Heather would.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Recovery Strategies -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-2">03 &middot; Recovery</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Recovery Strategies</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <em class="not-italic text-white/75 font-medium">Because nobody stays on the plan forever.</em>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            The data revealed three distinct patterns for how clients fall off and come back: crisis-driven
            returns (stress triggers a crash and a panicked re-engagement), long-term returns (months or
            years away, then a quiet comeback), and social reconnections (a life event or relationship
            brings them back to coaching).
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            The universal principle across all three: <strong class="text-white/80">zero judgment. Skip the
            re-education. Meet them exactly where they are.</strong> HeatherAI never guilt-trips a returning
            user. Never says "you should have stayed in touch." It picks up where you are right now and
            moves forward.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- The Coaching Arc -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-2">04 &middot; The Arc</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">The Coaching Arc</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <em class="not-italic text-white/75 font-medium">The right amount of coaching changes over time.</em>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            The most important pattern in the data wasn't about food — it was about the coaching
            relationship itself. We found a five-phase arc that repeats across thousands of clients:
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="text-[11px] text-accent font-bold tracking-wide shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-28">Months 1–3</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white/70">Intensive.</strong> Detailed feedback on every meal, specific substitutions, daily check-ins.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="text-[11px] text-accent font-bold tracking-wide shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-28">Months 4–8</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white/70">Building autonomy.</strong> Fewer prescriptions, more "what do you think?" questions. The client starts self-correcting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="text-[11px] text-accent font-bold tracking-wide shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-28">Months 9–18</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white/70">Maintenance.</strong> Situational check-ins, milestone celebrations, course corrections when needed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="text-[11px] text-accent font-bold tracking-wide shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-28">Months 18+</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white/70">Self-managing.</strong> The client is coaching themselves. Contact is situational, not daily.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="text-[11px] text-accent font-bold tracking-wide shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-28">After any gap</div>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white/70">Re-engagement.</strong> Zero judgment, meet them where they are, skip re-education.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mt-6">
            We call it <em class="not-italic text-white/75 font-medium">scaffold, then release</em>.
            HeatherAI knows where you are on the arc and adjusts its coaching intensity accordingly —
            prescriptive when you're new, progressively hands-off as you internalize the framework.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Weight Trajectory Intelligence -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-2">05 &middot; Weight Intelligence</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Weight Trajectory Intelligence</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <em class="not-italic text-white/75 font-medium">Thousands of real weight journeys — with the coaching context attached.</em>
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Most weight tracking tools show you a line going up or down. HeatherAI sees the story
            behind the line. Across thousands of clients, we mapped weight trajectories alongside the
            coaching conversations, life events, and interventions that produced them. We know what
            the 3-month plateau looks like before a breakthrough. We know what early regain signals
            look like after a successful loss phase. We know which coaching interventions correlate
            with sustained progress and which ones produce short-term results that don't hold.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            When you log your weight in HeatherAI, you're not just tracking a number — you're being
            compared against thousands of real journeys that looked like yours at this stage. That
            context is what turns a weigh-in into a coaching moment.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ SECTION 3: THE FRAMEWORKS ============ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">
          Heather's coaching language.<br />
          <em class="not-italic text-accent">Now embedded in AI.</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white/50 max-w-[680px] mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Over 20 years, Heather developed proprietary coaching frameworks — structured approaches
          to the recurring patterns she saw across thousands of clients. These frameworks are the
          intellectual property at the core of HeatherAI. They're what make it a coaching system,
          not a chatbot.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-3">The 10 Diet Devils</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            The ten most common behavioral patterns that derail nutrition goals. Each "devil"
            is a specific, recognizable scenario — not a vague concept — with a named
            counter-strategy Heather developed through thousands of real client interactions.
            When HeatherAI recognizes a Diet Devil in your conversation, it deploys the specific
            coaching response that Heather refined over two decades.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-3">The Six Catalysts to Overeating</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Heather identified six root causes that trigger overeating behavior — not the surface
            symptoms (stress, boredom, social pressure) but the underlying catalysts that create
            them. HeatherAI is built to diagnose before prescribing: it identifies which catalyst
            is active before offering a strategy, rather than giving generic advice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-3">Scaffold, Then Release</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Heather's core coaching methodology. Start intensive, build structure, then progressively
            release control as the client internalizes the framework. This isn't just a philosophy —
            it's a design principle embedded in HeatherAI's architecture. The AI adjusts its coaching
            posture over time, from prescriptive to collaborative to hands-off, mirroring Heather's
            real coaching cadence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-3">Zero-Judgment Re-engagement</h3>
          <p class="text-[13px] text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            Clients disappear — for weeks, months, sometimes years — and then come back. Heather's
            universal principle for handling returns: never guilt-trip, never restart from scratch,
            never say "you should have stayed in touch." Just meet them where they are right now
            and move forward. This principle is hardcoded into HeatherAI's re-engagement logic.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Pull quote -->
      <div class="mt-16 max-w-[680px] mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed italic">
          "Nutrition knowledge is everywhere. You can Google what to eat for breakfast. What you
          can't Google is what to do at 9pm on a Tuesday when the kids want pizza and you're
          exhausted and the plan says grilled chicken. That's coaching — and that's what these
          frameworks encode."
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ SECTION 4: THE SCIENCE ============ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">
          Peer-reviewed validation.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white/50 max-w-[680px] mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          The academic evidence is catching up to what Heather's clients have known for twenty years.
          Here's what the research says about the approach HeatherAI is built on.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">

        <!-- JAMA -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">JAMA &middot; December 2025</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">AI coaching matched human coaching outcomes over 12 months.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            A phase 3 randomized controlled trial from Johns Hopkins demonstrated that a fully automated
            AI lifestyle intervention was noninferior to human coaching across weight loss, physical
            activity, and metabolic health markers over a full year. This is the gold standard of clinical
            evidence — a phase 3 RCT published in the most authoritative medical journal — and it
            validates the entire category HeatherAI occupies.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[11px] text-white/30 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
            Mathioudakis et al. (2025). JAMA, 334(23):2079-2089. doi:10.1001/jama.2025.19563
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Verily -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">JMIR &middot; 2025 &middot; Verily / Google</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Methodology-grounded AI significantly outperforms generic LLMs.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            A study from Google's Verily life sciences team found that multi-agent AI workflows grounded
            in behavioral science frameworks were strongly preferred by expert evaluators over baseline
            LLM coaching. The key differentiator: specialized systems that identify root causes of dietary
            barriers before offering strategies. This directly validates HeatherAI's architecture — Heather's
            methodology embedded in the coaching logic, not a generic nutrition prompt.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[11px] text-white/30 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
            Yang et al. (2025). JMIR Formative Research, 9:e75421. doi:10.2196/75421
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Retention -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">Springer &middot; 2025 &middot; 21 Studies</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Hybrid AI + human coaching retains 57–92% of users.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            A systematic review of 21 studies including 8 RCTs found that hybrid AI + human coaching
            platforms consistently achieve the highest retention rates in digital health — ranging from
            57% to 92%. This supports HeatherAI's expert-in-the-loop design, and the
            <a href="/pricing" class="text-accent hover:underline">AI + Human Coach</a> tier, as
            both clinically and commercially optimal.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[11px] text-white/30 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
            Dunmore et al. (2025). Current Cardiovascular Risk Reports (Springer). doi:10.1007/s12170-025-00776-7
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Personalization -->
        <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[2px] font-semibold mb-3">Springer &middot; 2025 &middot; Longitudinal Study</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Personalized AI coaching increased engagement by 26%.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
            A 3-month longitudinal study of an AI-powered coaching assistant found that personalized
            interactions increased user engagement by 26% over non-personalized ones, and that
            conversational style increased average message length by more than 4×. Longer, more
            detailed messages mean richer context for the AI, better memory, and a stronger coaching
            relationship — the engagement flywheel HeatherAI is designed to create.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[11px] text-white/30 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
            Garcia-Zapirain et al. (2025). Journal of Healthcare Informatics Research (Springer). doi:10.1007/s41666-025-00217-5
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Honest caveat -->
      <div class="mt-12 max-w-[760px] mx-auto p-6 border border-white/[0.04] rounded-xl">
        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/60 mb-3">What the research doesn't yet prove.</h4>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-white/40 leading-relaxed">
          A 2025 JMIR systematic review limited to RCTs found limited statistically significant evidence
          for NLP chatbot interventions improving diet behavior specifically. This reflects the
          methodological immaturity of the field — small sample sizes and short study durations — not
          a negative finding about AI coaching efficacy. It's a reason to be precise about claims, and
          it's why HeatherAI is building its own outcome data alongside the published literature. We
          believe in showing the work.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[11px] text-white/25 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          Chen et al. (2025). JMIR mHealth and uHealth, 13:e66403. doi:10.2196/66403
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ CTA ============ -->
  <CtaSection
    headline={"See it for yourself."}
    subline="Start with free meal logging. Experience the coaching when you're ready."
  />

</BaseLayout>
